{"name": "hid", "metadata": {"name": "hid", "version": "1.0.6", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/apmorton/pyhidapi", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "ctypes bindings for hidapi", "upload_time": 1707597748}, "documentation": ["# Installing pyhidapi\npyhidapi is available on [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/hid/) and can be installed using pip.\n```\npip install hid\n```\n\npyhidapi is dependant upon the [hidapi library](https://github.com/libusb/hidapi), which must be installed separately.\n\n# Installing hidapi\n\n## Linux\nInstallation procedures vary depending on your distribution.\n\n### Arch Linux\nBinary distributions are available in the community repository.\n\n1. Enable the community repository in `/etc/pacman.conf`\n```\n[community]\nInclude = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist\n```\n2. Install hidapi\n```\npacman -Sy hidapi\n```\n\n### CentOS/RHEL\nBinary distributions are available through [EPEL](https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/EPEL).\n```\nyum install hidapi\n```\n\n### Fedora\nBinary distributions are available.\n```\ndnf install hidapi\n```\n\n### Ubuntu/Debian\nBinary distributions are available.\n\n```\napt install libhidapi-hidraw0\n```\nor\n```\napt install libhidapi-libusb0\n```\n\n### Others\nBinary distributions may be available in your package repositories. If not, you can build from source as described [in the libusb/hidapi README](https://github.com/libusb/hidapi#build-instructions).\n\n## Windows\nInstallation procedure for Windows is described [in the libusb/hidapi README](https://github.com/libusb/hidapi#building-on-windows)\n\nBinary distributions are provided by [libusb/hidapi](https://github.com/libusb/hidapi/releases)\n\n## OSX\nThere are currently no official binary distributions for Mac, so you must build hidapi yourself.\n\nInstallation instructions are described [in the libusb/hidapi README](https://github.com/libusb/hidapi#mac)\n\nYou can also use brew:\n```\nbrew install hidapi\n```\n\n## FreeBSD\nBinary distributions are available.\n\n```\npkg install -g 'py3*-hid'\n```\n\n# Sample usage code\n\nThe details about a HID device can be printed with following code:\n\n```python\nimport hid\n\nvid = 0x046d\t# Change it for your device\npid = 0xc534\t# Change it for your device\n\nwith hid.Device(vid, pid) as h:\n\tprint(f'Device manufacturer: {h.manufacturer}')\n\tprint(f'Product: {h.product}')\n\tprint(f'Serial Number: {h.serial}')\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "hid", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "hid.enumerate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "vid", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pid", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "hid.hidapi", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.library_paths", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.error", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_version.argtypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_version.restype", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.bus_type", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.bus_type", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.DeviceInfo._fields_", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_init.argtypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_init.restype", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_exit.argtypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hid.hidapi.hid_exit.restype", "type": null, "documen